noun.description: More fully "subclavius muscle". A muscle which (in humans) originates from the first costal cartilage and inserts on to the undersurface of the clavicle, acting to elevate the first rib or fix the clavicle.

origin: Early 17th century; earliest use found in Helkiah Crooke (1576–1648), physician and anatomist. From post-classical Latin subclavius, use as noun (short for subclavius musculus) of subclavius, adjective.
